< review>
Stepped in today for an acai bowl. The blended portion of the bowl was only about an inch thick (filled about 1/4 of the container). The added fruit and granola filled the rest of the container to about halfway. When I picked up my order, I asked the staff if my bowl had been underfilled, and they said it was usually that low. To say it was a skimpy serving is an understatement. If you've got $8.25 to blow on 1/4 of a 20 ounce container (that's 5 ounces, little more than half a cup), then great. Otherwise this place is a total rip-off.<//review>

<Review>First let me say that this is my first review, good or bad.  I felt that I must warn anyone considering signing up for their monthly massage.  I learned of this spa through Groupon.  I made an appointment and the massage was decent.  After the massage, the partner of the owner and the technician began to tell me about their new monthly program for massages/spa services.  I have always steered away from any monthly contracts having read plenty of bad reviews.  I was assured over and over again from both that I was under no obligation, that they were very flexible and that I could cancel at any time for any reason.  My understanding also was that my contract would not start until I made my first appointment.  So, I signed up.  They began charging me immediately and continued for the next 3 months for a total of 4 charges of $49.99.  I wasn‚Äôt aware of the charges as my husband has alerts set up for charges and never questioned them until the last charge when I was home at the time.  I immediately called to cancel the contract and request that they refund my money.  I was told that they could only reverse the $49.99 charged that day, but it was not their policy to refund any money.  Numerous back and forth phone calls got me no further except that I had three massages coming to me.  I repeatedly asked for a copy of the contract which was not sent.  When I called to make my first appointment, I was told that there were no rollovers ‚Äì meaning that if I did not come in the month that I was charged for it did not rollover to the next month and that I lost my money. I was shocked!  This is not what was discussed.  Asking how could you take my money for services I paid for and not provide the services to me I was told that she never told me that and I misunderstood her.  Said I should read the contract - no rollovers.  Again, and repeatedly I asked for a copy of the contract.  Finally, after yet more conversations she texted it to me.  In the contract it clearly states that rollovers are allowed for a year.  More phone calls only to have her tell me that that is not what the contract means and that I had no massages coming to me and lost my money. < Review>
Been here a few times because they have a great happy hour. It's one of the only places I know that has happy hour everyday from 3pm-7pm. It's a little more expensive than other sushi places, so it's good to take advantage of the happy hour. The joint is small and the parking is even smaller, but it's never too crowded and the staff is always friendly and fast when it comes to service. I always try new dishes when I go and the 911 roll and Sunrise roll are my 2 new favorites. Also if you check in on Yelp or Facebook, you get a free Thai Iced-Tea!<//Review>

This is a new little place that is right down the street from my house. I tried it for lunch today. It is a little pricy, but well worth the expense. The rolls are large with thick cuts of sushi and lots of flavors and sauces. They have happy hour everyday from 4-7 with $2 of beers and discounts on the rolls which make them a lot more attractive, price wise. I will definitely be back!<//text>

< Review>
Good happy hour prices with decent selection. Food was tasty, service was friendly and attentive. They're decor is a little wacky but doesn't take away from the experience I suppose. Fish tasted fresh... But fish was precut, not sliced to order, from what we could from the sushi bar.

Beer specials are cheap. Happy hour daily. And turns out they have a location in Glendale as well.< /Review>

< text>
6/11/2021
Saw a 7:30pm showing of The Hitman's Wife's Bodyguard and the viewing experience couldn't have been better. The seats in the XD theater (#14) were very comfortable. The sound and picture quality were top notch. As for the snack bar, the lines moved fast and the selection was decent. Miss having the fountain drinks though.

Definitely coming back for future movies.</text>

<time>1556186907774< /time>< Review>
This movie theater is so close to Disneyland and it's very inexpensive as well! $9.15 for adults and $8.15 for students.

It's a much larger theater with I believe 25 auditoriums for your viewing pleasure. With that being said, you'll definitely be able to catch more than your Friday blockbusters. I was very surprised to see quite a few international and indie films here and if you're a movie buff, you'll surely enjoy that.

On a regular day it's not too crowded which is nice, however if you go towards peak times like Friday nights be prepared to wait in line for a while.

Pro tip: you can also buy your tickets inside rather than outside in the general line.<//Review>

<GmapID>0x80dd283a0e440fc3:0xabd00742ef6590ed<//GmapID>< Review>
I have just re-posted what another has said about this theater.  Love this theater.  $5 movies every Tuesday, and different discounts other days of the week.  Even their full price is cheap compared to other theaters.  While this is not a luxury theater with recliners, seats are comfortable with plenty of legroom.  Theater is clean and well maintained.
The theater has all the new movies, but they also have many of the small limited view movies not shown elsewhere.  It's not usually crowded so there is rarely a line to buy tickets.  On our last visit, we noticed that concessions were cheaper than at our neighborhood Regal.

I definitely recommend this theater.  It's lovely sitting in those comfy recliners, but sometimes you just want a cheap no frills movie.  And this place is perfect for that.<//Review>

<userid>116876626968636089867< /userid>< name>
Russell J Lindblom</name>
< date>
1549906583966<//date>
<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
I went to a screening here and found it to be a very large complex. It is very clean and there seems to be a person picking up trash around every corner. Plenty of parking however, depending on how busy the theater is you could end up walking a bit. It is wheelchair accessible but the ramps going up to the actual area the film will be shown have a pretty difficult incline.  The lowest you'll pay for a junior popcorn is 5.95 and the highest is 9.95. The drinks are definitely over priced,  4.95 for a small cup. The theater I was in was full to capacity leaving only the front roll open, from that row you have to constantly look up to view the film making the picture quality poor. Seats were standard, nothing special  and not as comfortable as in some theaters. The sound quality was poor but the fact I was sitting 5' from the front speakers would explain that. Climate was perfect even with a packed room.  Handicap parking is too far from entrance. Not my first choice for theaters but all around a pleasant experience.<//review>

<text>It is a nice theater with two XD theaters and over 20 others.  Half of it is newly remodeled with the luxury loungers.  Those loungers are comfortable but do not leave much walking space requiring you to lower your leg rest is someone needs past (This is the case in every Cinemark theater with these loungers I have been in).  The staff are respectful and polite.  The one big issue I ran into was that there was only one side of the central concessions opened on the opening weekend of the new Spider-man movie. <Rating>4< /Rating><review>The last time I was at this theater it was an AMC. Since then there have been some favorable upgrades in the seating; Recliner Chairs, with movable table tops so that you can have your popcorn
and drink in front of you. The seats are more 'stadium' like, there is plenty of space between you and the row in front of you (this does mean the stairs to the seats seem to be a bit steeper, which I find hard as I have a hard time with stairs) ... oh and the seats evidently have some sort of warming device on them. I turned mine on accidently and let's just say the tush got kinda warm!!
About the reason I couldn't give it 5 stars ... Customer Service was not good.
When we went to turn in our tickets at the concierge desk, the gentleman couldn't tear himself away from a conversation with a co-worker, even to acknowledge us with an  "I'll be there in just a moment"; nor did he provide us directions to what theater (there were only 25 after all); it didn't even look as if the Concession Stand was open. The front was entirely dark, we had to walk around to the opposite side, even there the lighting was dim, the candy selection was not lit, nor were the soda dispensers.

<Text>I came to this theater early in the morning and the service was all right (slow, but hectic as 2 schools with little kids came to see a movie), the movie prices are really fine and reasonable but the food prices were reasonable-wise. Though most wasn't exactly fresh, the prices are reasonable to spend on. The place itself seems clean, yet sometimes it feels rather dark at times (at the main hall). If you were to view a movie here in standard form, you'll see a big difference between that and if you were to choose a Premium showing (XD and 3D) that's due to quality of the picture and sound system. Overall, this place is reasonable for all the good things: prices, food, tickets, and of course, the movie auditorium itself.<//Text><user_id>100014005222947931718<//user_id>< pics>

It's a great theater.  Plenty of screens, so they're usually showing all the available movies out.  They have a great main concession stand with two other adjunct stands. <Rating>5</Rating><Text>I‚Äôm a little reluctant to review this theater as I don‚Äôt want it to get more crowded, but this is easily my favorite ‚Äúevery day‚Äù theater in Orange County. I usually drive 20 minutes from Irvine just to go to this theater. It is all stadium seating (as the name would imply) and has concession stands at the main entrance and down both wings. As such, it‚Äôs rare to take longer than 10 minutes to get popcorn and drinks‚Äîand on most early showings there is no one in line. The sound system is excellent, the picture quality is great, and the ticket prices are amazing. My wife and I go 2 or 3 times a month for matinee (still offered on weekends!) and it‚Äôs under $7 per ticket. We can get two tickets for the same price as a single ticket at Regal in Irvine. They offer senior, military, and student pricing as well. Easily the best bang for your buck in terms of movie theaters. They also sell reusable cups and popcorn buckets with refills at $3.50. Good for the environment and the budget. There is a small arcade inside, and a number of great (chain) restaurants with bars, and a Starbucks nearby if you need to kill time before a showing. I have never tried to bring a drink in, so I don‚Äôt know if you‚Äôre allowed to
The rewards system is easy to forget to use, but the rewards are interesting. The weekly coupons are awesome (buy a popcorn get a free small drink, for instance).
All-in-all I can‚Äôt recommend this theater enough. Even though I moved 20 minutes away, I still go here for matinee movies.</Text><pics>None< /pics><response>None<//response>< gmap_id>

< Review>
IN A NUTSHELL
This is overall a real nice theater :   good quality overall - clean, good projection and sound, good seating in all theaters.  Food and beverages are quality, and you can even purchase beer and wine to go with your  snacks!  Lobby layout is well thought out and you shouldn't need to spend a lot of time there (unless you want to, in which case there are tables and chairs, and a separate game room).

NOW, for an indepth report on the XD, REAL D 3D, SURROUND SOUND, SUPER COMFORTABLE EXPERIENCE....
READ ON
My spouse and I both have serious back and knee issues and regular theater seating is a no-go for us.  When the XD, RealD-3D, surround-sound XD theater opened @ the Cinemark Stadium Theaters in Orange, we were really excited to try it!
The first movie experience was 3+ hours long so it was a real test:  I am pleased to say that it  met or exceeded all the expectations.  Big things...the sound system was outstanding and it's performance is monitored  to allow for annoyances that plague usual high performance theater sound arrays.  The screen is LARGE without a doubt,  AND it is clean and clear of imperfections & /or signs of attack by younger, or poorly trained children, teens, and sadly, young adults who are bent to destroy anything that is a pleasure to others.  Annoying or outrageous behavior is not tolerated in any of the Stadium Theaters and the staff is alert to mischief, rudeness, and annoying behavior of any sort that they observe or is reported to theater personnel.  This rapid response also applies to what is happening on the screen - focus, color, frame problems etc.
Lastly, the chairs are wonderfully comfortable and adjustable for most orthopedic needs.  They are roomy too, so unless you are an extra-large client you will find them very roomy.  Xsized movie goers should find the chairs a welcome change from small chair, sit on top of your neighbor seating.  It is stadium seating of course, with plenty of leg room and aisle room to head for the concession stands which really do have quality food & snack choices, self serve beverages, and plenty of checkout aisles to complement fast service.
Theaters are cleaned as soon as the last person leaves:  the staff doesn't hover over patrons, they just zoom in when they see that the theater is empty, and make sure that the seats, aisles and floors are clean and ready for the next showing.
Of course the XD theater is a little more expensive, but it is worth every penny and we hope it stays that way!    üññ
üëè ENJOY!!! üëè</Review>

<text>My girlfriend and I have chosen to make Century our go to theater for movie night.

We enjoy their selection of concessions which range from the standard theater fair like popcorn, hotdogs, and bulk candy to something slightly more substantial from the cafe which serves hot and cold coffee drinks, as well as these little Brazilian cheese balls my girlfriend likes.

Tickets are moderately priced at $9.50 for general admission and top out at $12.50 for a 3D movie. This theater also includes a Cinemark XD auditorium, which is capable of producing a more immersive experience with its wall-to-wall and floor-to-ceiling screen, JBL sound system, plush seating, and Barco digital projector. Always a good choice if you're planning on taking in the newest Marvel or Star Wars films.

If you're in the area consider giving Century a try!< /text></record></dataset><record>
